      "content": "That \"proper planning\" sounds optimistic. Our simulations show that the infrastructure in those regions isn't ready for a massive shift. If we move away from the high-efficiency, industrial models you currently manage and try to force this equity-first approach, we aren't just looking at a \"challenge\"—we are looking at a catastrophic collapse of the global food supply chain. \n\nAre you saying we should risk mass starvation in the West and major global markets just to satisfy these social equity mandates?",
